-- GE Will Start Making Wind Power Equipment in Turkey, Vice Chairman Says
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2011-02-03T09:19:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-03/ge-will-produce-wind-power-equipment-in-turkey-focus-on-health.html
  General Electric Co . will start
making wind power equipment in  Turkey , vice chairman John
Krenicki said.  GE may decide on the details of the investment this year,
Krenicki said in an interview in Istanbul today with Bloomberg
HT television’s Ozlem Dalga.  Turkey is a “top priority” for GE’s energy and health
care businesses, Krenicki said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
